The paper focuses on transfer learning in paralinguistic tasks, specifically speaker, emotion, and gender recognition. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.SD (sound), cs.CL (computation and language), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.CV (computer vision), and cs.AI (artificial intelligence). However, since the paper deals with audio data and focuses on deep learning methods, cs.SD and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also compares progressive neural networks to conventional deep learning methods, which further supports the likelihood of cs.SD and cs.CL as the primary sub-categories.
